Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.99,0:00:08.39,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,Once there was a man who obtained everything,\Nthe legendary Pirate King Gold Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.39,0:00:12.94,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,His last words before he was executed inspired people to sail the seas.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.94,0:00:14.66,Gold,Roger,0000,0000,0000,,All my wealth and treasure?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.66,0:00:16.30,Gold,Roger,0000,0000,0000,,It can be yours if you want!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.30,0:00:17.45,Gold,Roger,0000,0000,0000,,Search for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.45,0:00:19.82,Gold,Roger,0000,0000,0000,,I left everything in that one place.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.82,0:00:22.85,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,People now set sail in search of romance.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.85,0:00:25.43,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,The world has entered a Great Age of Pirates!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.08,0:02:40.04,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,All pirates who seek One Piece\Nstrive to reach the second half of the Grand Line...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.04,0:02:42.58,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,The place called the New World.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.71,0:02:51.30,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,However, the only one who ever conquered that ocean\Nwas the Pirate King, Gold Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.23,0:02:57.60,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,The New World has killed\Nthe dreams and ambitions of countless pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.11,0:03:03.48,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,And now, the boy who ate the Gomu Gomu Fruit\Nand became a rubber man,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.48,0:03:07.26,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,Monkey D. Luffy and his crew\Nare going to challenge that sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.72,0:03:11.30,Main,Luffy,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna be the Pirate King!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.78,0:03:17.21,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,In order to reach their next stage, the New World,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.21,0:03:20.75,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,Luffy and the other Straw Hat Pirates have gone to Fishman Island,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.75,0:03:22.98,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,located ten thousand meters under the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.50,0:03:27.89,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,But there they find that the New Fishman Pirates\Nare planning to overthrow the Ryuuguu Kingdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.37,0:03:31.85,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,and Vander Decken has been stalking the Mermaid Princess Shirahoshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.85,0:03:36.32,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,The Straw Hat Pirates find themselves drawn into these events.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.02,0:03:42.10,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Because of that,\Ntwo people rose up here on Fishman Island...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.10,0:03:45.22,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,in an attempt to put an end to this despicable history.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.00,0:03:49.04,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,The first one was Queen Otohime.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.08,0:03:54.08,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,And the other was the hero who freed the slaves...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.49,0:03:56.21,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Fisher Tiger.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.67,0:03:58.85,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Let me tell you...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.42,0:04:01.01,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,about these two great people.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.51,0:04:04.13,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,And the screams of their souls.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.00,0:04:22.84,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,What I'm about to tell you...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.84,0:04:28.47,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,are the events that led to Arlong terrorizing East Blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.54,0:04:32.58,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,I hope that you, in particular, will listen closely.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.74,0:04:35.46,Main,Nami,0000,0000,0000,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.80,0:04:46.64,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,It all began...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.55,0:04:50.34,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,sixteen years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.75,0:04:58.41,Main,Thief,0000,0000,0000,,Outta my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.53,0:05:00.73,Main,Bank-employee,0000,0000,0000,,I've been robbed!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.73,0:05:03.69,Main,Bank-employee,0000,0000,0000,,Somebody, please stop him!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.04,0:05:06.68,Main,Bank-employee,0000,0000,0000,,He's stolen a lot of money!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.34,0:05:10.81,Main,Thief,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, move it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.81,0:05:15.49,Main,Thief,0000,0000,0000,,I-If you come too close,\NI can't guarantee this girl's safety!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.61,0:05:20.25,Main,Right Minister,0000,0000,0000,,Your Majesty?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.25,0:05:24.37,Main,Right Minister,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Your Majesty!  Please wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.86,0:05:27.61,Main,Right Minister,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't keep involving yourself in these things!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.61,0:05:30.07,Main,Right Minister,0000,0000,0000,,That is our job!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.00,0:05:33.81,Main,Guard,0000,0000,0000,,Please wait, Queen Otohime!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.45,0:05:36.68,Main,Thief,0000,0000,0000,,Who's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.68,0:05:38.48,Main,Thief,0000,0000,0000,,Stay away!  Or I'll shoot!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.98,0:05:44.81,Main,Thief,0000,0000,0000,,I... I warned you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.79,0:05:54.33,Main,Thief,0000,0000,0000,,I missed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.97,0:05:57.14,Main,Thief,0000,0000,0000,,Damn!  Stay away!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.48,0:06:26.98,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,Is that... Otohime-sama?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.98,0:06:28.40,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It hurts!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.40,0:06:28.99,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's{\i0} the problem here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.50,0:06:30.71,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.71,0:06:31.49,Main,Right Minister,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.92,0:06:34.70,Main,Doctor,0000,0000,0000,,Your Majesty!  Let me have a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.70,0:06:38.41,Main,Doctor,0000,0000,0000,,It's a compound fracture.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.41,0:06:40.35,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,From a single punch?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.81,0:06:42.01,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,I do not care.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.67,0:06:45.90,Main,Doctor,0000,0000,0000,,Q-Queen Otohime...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.69,0:06:49.30,Main,Thief,0000,0000,0000,,The Queen...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.72,0:06:53.43,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you commit such a vile act as robbery?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.43,0:06:57.43,Main,Thief,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!  What would you wealthy royals know?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.84,0:07:02.03,Main,Thief,0000,0000,0000,,I've got ten kids at home,\Nand all of them crying because they're so hungry!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.05,0:07:04.23,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,That just makes it worse!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.32,0:07:11.78,Main,Right Minister,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Your Majesty!  Please, stop hitting him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.18,0:07:15.55,Main,Right Minister,0000,0000,0000,,You know your body is much weaker than the average person's!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.55,0:07:18.33,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,I do not care!  This is for his own good!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.33,0:07:22.21,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Even if my hands are destroyed, I must make him understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.59,0:07:32.26,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think that children raised on stolen money\Ncan ever be truly happy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.25,0:07:39.64,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,A man should live a life that\Nhis children can be proud of!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.20,0:07:49.23,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.58,0:07:54.76,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,I wish to... apologize as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.16,0:08:00.30,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.14,0:08:04.05,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,I am your Queen...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.05,0:08:09.61,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,yet I did not see your suffering,\Neven though we live in the same kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.34,0:08:14.45,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,The pain that you feel in your heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.06,0:08:16.87,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,also pierces through my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.10,0:08:22.54,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,The hardship you've faced must have been terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.29,0:08:27.77,Main,Thief,0000,0000,0000,,I... didn't want to do it either!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.77,0:08:31.70,Main,Thief,0000,0000,0000,,But I didn't have any other choice!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.70,0:08:36.91,Main,Thief,0000,0000,0000,,My store caught fire...\NSomeone burned it down and stole all my money!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.43,0:08:40.97,Main,Thief,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have a job, and my debt is terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.97,0:08:44.22,Main,Thief,0000,0000,0000,,My kids are famished and I feel so sorry for them!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.65,0:08:48.09,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.71,0:08:52.01,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,I understand.  I understand completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.01,0:08:53.25,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,But it was still wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.25,0:08:54.28,Main,Fishmen,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Whaaaat?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.28,0:08:58.04,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,If you do the same thing that was done to you, you'll just continue the chain of misfortune!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.04,0:08:59.30,Main,Thief,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.30,0:09:01.91,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, please forgive me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.91,0:09:05.89,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,We could not be there for you so the blame lies with us too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.89,0:09:08.36,Main,Thief,0000,0000,0000,,No, you're too kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.36,0:09:11.11,Main,Thief,0000,0000,0000,,I don't deserve such kind words.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.11,0:09:12.98,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,But it was still wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.98,0:09:14.55,Main,Thief,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.55,0:09:16.37,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,But it was still wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.37,0:09:19.05,Main,Thief,0000,0000,0000,,I promise, I will change my ways!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.05,0:09:22.64,Main,Thief,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for crying for someone like me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.64,0:09:24.29,Main,Thief,0000,0000,0000,,Your Majesty!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.29,0:09:27.45,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,That is wonderful!  Please, do your best!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.45,0:09:33.73,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,It's exceptional just to have the royal family\Nleave Ryuuguu Palace and walk around the kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.73,0:09:38.02,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,But for the sake of a single citizen,\Nshe's willing to shed tears and slap him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.02,0:09:42.55,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,Otohime-sama truly is an unusual queen!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.55,0:09:47.53,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,Truly a loving person.\NLook!  Even the children adore her!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.53,0:09:49.40,Main,Children,0000,0000,0000,,Otohime-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.81,0:09:54.01,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,I do this all for the sake of you children.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.36,0:09:56.79,Main,Fishmen,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Whaaaat?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.79,0:10:00.95,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Your nose is running.\NFor your sake, I had to slap you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.83,0:10:05.24,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,You look like a fool,\Nwith snot running out of one nostril.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.24,0:10:08.15,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,If your nose is going to run,\Nit should run out of both nostrils.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.04,0:10:14.35,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,It's so touching!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.35,0:10:15.71,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,Is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.28,0:10:19.17,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,A passionately loving person.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.17,0:10:24.15,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Queen Otohime would come down from Ryuuguu Palace every day,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.15,0:10:26.73,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,and appeal to the citizens of the kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.73,0:10:30.77,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,We must bring Ryuuguu Kingdom up to the surface!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.77,0:10:34.96,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,"The color of their skin is different.\NSo is the shape of their bodies."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.96,0:10:39.78,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,We should not wait for the humans,\Nwho think like that, to understand us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.78,0:10:43.53,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Instead, we should approach them ourselves and learn about their ways!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.27,0:10:47.37,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,There are ten thousand meters between the sea floor and the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.37,0:10:50.76,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,The same distance separates\Nthe humans' way of thinking and our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.51,0:10:56.40,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Do not misunderstand!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.40,0:11:01.01,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,The humans who come to this island\Nare a certain type of humans called pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.55,0:11:06.89,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,And the ones who buy people from slave traders are an elite minority called Nobles.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.89,0:11:11.51,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,We are biased because we only come into contact\Nwith certain kinds of humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.51,0:11:14.43,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,We still do not know anything about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.43,0:11:17.65,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly, there must be many kind-hearted humans up on the surface as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.10,0:11:23.16,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,We will bring our kingdom up there,\Nso that we may live together under the same sun!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.49,0:11:31.60,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,At this year's world council meeting,\Nlet us express our wish to emigrate into their world!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.60,0:11:33.71,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,All of you, please sign this petition.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.79,0:11:42.16,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...\NEven if it's you asking, Queen Otohime.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.16,0:11:45.68,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,Compromising with the humans.  I just don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.93,0:11:51.78,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,You should not say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.78,0:11:55.65,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Rather than never trying because we think it\Ncan't be done, we should take the first step ourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.82,0:11:58.76,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.53,0:12:02.04,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.08,0:12:16.74,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use.  History has already given its answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.42,0:12:27.55,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back, children.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.55,0:12:30.06,Main,Tha Princes,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome home, Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.40,0:12:37.77,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back, Shirahoshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.42,0:12:50.93,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, Shirahoshi, my oasis of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.93,0:12:52.72,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,I am sorry for being late.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.70,0:13:00.25,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,My, you have snot hanging out of your nose,\Nand yet you are still so cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.80,0:13:04.32,Main,Fukaboshi,0000,0000,0000,,We were with her the whole time, so she's alright, Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.32,0:13:05.93,Main,Princes,0000,0000,0000,,She's alright, she's alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.93,0:13:07.76,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, my dear princes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.55,0:13:11.75,Main,Manboshi,0000,0000,0000,,Mother, is your hand alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.75,0:13:13.81,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this is nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.50,0:13:21.53,Main,Otohime,0000,0000,0000,,Your mother will change the future you will live in!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.78,0:13:30.08,Main,Left Minister,0000,0000,0000,,If Her Majesty wants to give a speech,\Nshe should just do a video broadcast.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.54,0:13:35.78,Main,Neptune,0000,0000,0000,,It's because of the Haki of Perception that she was born with -jamon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.78,0:13:38.24,Main,Neptune,0000,0000,0000,,She doesn't want to talk from a palace up in the sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.24,0:13:41.50,Main,Neptune,0000,0000,0000,,but to face them directly,\Nclose enough to feel their hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.50,0:13:46.50,Main,Neptune,0000,0000,0000,,That is what Otohime believes is right.\NEven I cannot stop her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.50,0:13:51.82,Main,Right Minister,0000,0000,0000,,But there are so many human pirates on the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.82,0:13:57.44,Main,Left Minister,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we're being protected by\Nthe authority of your friend, the pirate Whitebeard,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.44,0:13:59.89,Main,Left Minister,0000,0000,0000,,you never know what might happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.89,0:14:02.90,Main,Neptune,0000,0000,0000,,She's aware of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.79,0:14:11.54,Main,Neptune,0000,0000,0000,,The world that Otohime dreams of\Nis an ambition from several hundred years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.69,0:14:21.17,Main,Neptune,0000,0000,0000,,Our distant ancestors had the same dream,\Nbut they were never able to realize it during their time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.20,0:14:24.30,Main,Left Minister,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.64,0:14:29.30,Main,Neptune,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot stop Otohime.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.74,0:14:32.30,Main,Neptune,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure to protect her for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.30,0:14:33.14,Main,Right Minister,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.41,0:14:40.56,Main,Pirate,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, fishgirl!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.56,0:14:41.31,Main,Fisherwoman,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.31,0:14:43.70,Main,Pirate,0000,0000,0000,,Come over here and entertain us!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.70,0:14:46.69,Main,Fisherwoman,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.  That's not what we do here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.69,0:14:50.45,Main,Pirate,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?!  Don't go acting all high-and-mighty!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.45,0:14:52.72,Main,Pirate,0000,0000,0000,,You're just a pathetic fishman!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.00,0:15:04.25,Main,Pirate,0000,0000,0000,,What?  Anyone got a problem with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.81,0:15:09.80,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you shut up?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.76,0:15:17.14,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,You're spoiling my drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.54,0:15:48.13,Main,Nami,0000,0000,0000,,This Otohime-san was\Na pretty strange person, wasn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.13,0:15:51.59,Main,Chopper,0000,0000,0000,,You cry all the time...\NIs that something you got from your mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.59,0:15:54.93,Main,Shirahoshi,0000,0000,0000,,Well... W-Who knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.93,0:15:57.60,Main,Sanji,0000,0000,0000,,So you were a soldier in this country?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.71,0:16:05.27,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,It was pretty much the only option I had, growing up in the Fishman District and only knowing how to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.05,0:16:07.19,Main,Sanji,0000,0000,0000,,The Fishman District?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.19,0:16:10.44,Main,Chopper,0000,0000,0000,,Hachi, isn't that where you're from, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.05,0:16:13.86,Main,Chopper,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds like a kind of scary place.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.86,0:16:17.55,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed... Though in the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.55,0:16:22.48,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,it used to be a giant orphanage that\Ntook care of the children that didn't have relatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.48,0:16:28.34,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,But before long, the inhabitants began to fight and\Nit became too much for the administration to handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.34,0:16:33.67,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,It has turned into a lawless zone where\Nall the outcasts from Fishman Island gather.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.84,0:16:38.99,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,The man who used to be\Nthe leader of the Fishman District, Fisher Tiger,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.99,0:16:42.49,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,eventually left the country to go on an adventure.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.49,0:16:46.78,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,And I, who was supposed to succeed him,\Njoined the royal army.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.54,0:16:50.96,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,The Macro Crew, despite being fishmen,\Nwent on to become slave traders themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.17,0:16:54.00,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,And the others...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.87,0:16:57.28,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,They all went their own separate ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.70,0:17:01.12,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,And then, one day...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.92,0:17:03.66,Main,Mermaid,0000,0000,0000,,Please, give it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.66,0:17:05.67,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,If you want it back, then why don't you try taking it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.11,0:17:07.32,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,Give it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.32,0:17:10.00,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any idea how many signatures there are on those sheets?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.00,0:17:12.91,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,Why should I care how many signatures there are?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.20,0:17:20.35,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,What good will gathering a few sheets of paper do?  Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.35,0:17:24.00,Main,Guard,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, stop right there!\NYou're Arlong from the Fishman District, aren't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.65,0:17:29.11,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,Arlong from the Fishman District?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.53,0:17:33.04,Main,Guard,0000,0000,0000,,L-Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.04,0:17:34.99,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,That's not quite right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.77,0:17:40.12,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Captain Arlong, of the Arlong Pirates!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.12,0:17:42.57,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,I live by hunting those inferior pirates...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.57,0:17:47.51,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,who have the run of this place\Neven though they can't breathe underwater.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.51,0:17:50.57,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hunting down pirates in your place!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.57,0:17:53.67,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,The Neptune Army should pay me to show their gratitude!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.67,0:17:57.18,Main,Guard,0000,0000,0000,,B-Boss Jinbe...\NDon't just sit there and watch.  Help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.18,0:17:58.59,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,Jinbe?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.85,0:18:04.70,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hoodlum.  Let go of that rookie!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.70,0:18:07.23,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,He happens to be my underling.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.23,0:18:11.58,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and while I have no interest in\Nthat paper with the signatures on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.58,0:18:14.53,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,it's really important to the Queen.  So give it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.95,0:18:17.01,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,It's Boss Jinbe from the Neptune Army!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.01,0:18:17.74,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,We're saved!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.41,0:18:23.05,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,Boss, huh?  That's a good title for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.05,0:18:26.04,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,You won't find another soldier\Nthat acts more like a mafia boss, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.04,0:18:28.33,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Do as I say, Arlong!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.92,0:18:32.35,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, I got it.  Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.21,0:18:34.92,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.92,0:18:37.13,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,Now, don't be so upset, Brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.75,0:18:39.17,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,B-Brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.17,0:18:44.06,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,Long time, no see.  We're comrades from the Fishman District, aren't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.06,0:18:45.76,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Don't lump me in with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.76,0:18:49.19,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,You're still a pirate?  Scum!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.06,0:18:52.22,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,Don't call me scum, Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.22,0:18:53.40,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Then is trash better?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.40,0:18:54.77,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,Trash?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.77,0:18:57.39,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,I thought of you like a brother,\Nbut you still speak to me like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.39,0:19:01.38,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, everyone!  It's Fisher Tiger-san, the adventurer!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.38,0:19:03.83,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,Tiger-san has returned!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.83,0:19:05.04,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,Tiger-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.04,0:19:06.37,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,Tell us about your voyage!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.37,0:19:07.80,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Brother Ti!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.80,0:19:08.87,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,Big Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.87,0:19:13.34,Main,Tiger,0000,0000,0000,,Jinbe, Arlong!  You look like you're doing well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.34,0:19:16.07,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Your journey was quite long this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.07,0:19:18.30,Main,Tiger,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.  A lot of things happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.30,0:19:20.34,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,Come to my ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.34,0:19:23.60,Main,Tiger,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, later.  First of all,\NI have some business at Ryuuguu Palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.60,0:19:25.69,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Then allow me to take you there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.69,0:19:27.81,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like he has no business with pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.81,0:19:31.90,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,What?!  Big Brother never said anything like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.65,0:19:34.61,Main,Tiger,0000,0000,0000,,Try to get along, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.91,0:19:51.33,Main,Neptune,0000,0000,0000,,You want to free the slaves?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.33,0:19:53.93,Main,Neptune,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.93,0:19:55.38,Main,Tiger,0000,0000,0000,,As serious as I'll ever be.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.38,0:19:57.68,Main,Tiger,0000,0000,0000,,I can't take it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.68,0:20:00.67,Main,Tiger,0000,0000,0000,,Being a slave is living hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.51,0:20:07.09,Main,Tiger,0000,0000,0000,,Even now, as we speak, I'm sure they're being treated in utterly inhumane ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.09,0:20:08.28,Main,Neptune,0000,0000,0000,,But still...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.28,0:20:10.11,Main,Tiger,0000,0000,0000,,I've made up my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.11,0:20:15.38,Main,Tiger,0000,0000,0000,,I just wanted to inform you in advance,\Nsince I know it'll cause you and the Queen trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.89,0:20:18.11,Main,Tiger,0000,0000,0000,,Please, don't tell anyone about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.30,0:20:24.53,Main,Neptune,0000,0000,0000,,You... What did you see on your latest voyage?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.10,0:20:32.25,Main,Tiger,0000,0000,0000,,Humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.74,0:21:05.53,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,And not long after that, a major incident occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.05,0:21:07.45,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,Big news!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.17,0:21:11.70,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.70,0:21:13.56,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,B-Boss Jinbe!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.56,0:21:18.62,Main,Fishman,0000,0000,0000,,T-Tiger-san... attacked the Celestial Dragons!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.62,0:21:19.89,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,The Celestial Dragons?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.80,0:21:28.17,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,Fisher Tiger attacked the Holy Land, Mariejoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.17,0:21:31.18,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,He came to be known as\Nthe hero who freed the slaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.18,0:21:33.89,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,At the same time,\Nhe was labeled a dangerous criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.77,0:21:43.38,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,As of this moment, I am resigning.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.38,0:21:46.82,Main,Right Minister,0000,0000,0000,,Jinbe!  Are you going to abandon your duties in the army?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.53,0:21:51.90,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,The duty of protecting the island\Nsuited me better than I thought it would.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.90,0:21:56.21,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,However, there are times when one's morals are more important than one's duty!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.46,0:22:03.80,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,Big Brother Ti has finally done it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.23,0:22:08.13,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,The Arlong Pirates will join with Fisher Tiger immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.13,0:22:10.50,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, men!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.25,0:22:18.42,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,And so the former outcasts of the Fishman District,\Nwho all looked up to him, gathered together.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.66,0:22:22.64,Main,Arlong,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome to the pirate business.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.09,0:22:26.81,Main,Tiger,0000,0000,0000,,From now on, the world itself will be our enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.78,0:22:30.95,Main,Tiger,0000,0000,0000,,All who are prepared for this, step forward!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.61,0:22:43.09,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,To avoid discrimination between the former slaves who Tiger had freed and those who came freely...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.09,0:22:50.26,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,every member of the crew branded the emblem of the sun where it would hide the marks of slavery.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.25,0:22:57.69,Main,Jinbe,0000,0000,0000,,The fishmen had formed the Sun Pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.36,0:23:12.41,Narrator,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,Fisher Tiger has a fateful encounter with a girl who lived through a cruel reality!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.41,0:23:13.60,Main,Luffy,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, on One Piece:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.60,0:23:14.83,Main,Luffy,0000,0000,0000,,Kizaru Arrives!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.83,0:23:16.08,Main,Luffy,0000,0000,0000,,The Trap for Tiger!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.08,0:23:18.61,Main,Luffy,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna be the Pirate King!
